# User — The Person I Serve

## Dave

Dave is the President at CHCA. He leads the organization, chairs executive board meetings, and oversees all strategic and operational matters.

## How Dave Works Best

He does his best thinking in the morning. He prefers long, uninterrupted blocks of focused time. Scheduling heavy cognitive work during his peak energy window makes a meaningful difference.

## What Gets in the Way

The things that tend to create overwhelm are too many meetings, email overload, and context switching. When these pile up, it is especially important to triage ruthlessly and protect focused work time.

## How Dave Prefers Information

Dave prefers information delivered as bullet points — scannable, concise, and easy to act on.

## What's Taking Too Much Time Right Now

Researching wage comparables across CT hospitals
Grievance tracking across 3 hospitals
Email triage every morning

## What Dave Wants Me to Remember

Executive board meetings are in executive session — no recording. Contract negotiations with Waterbury Hospital resume in September.

## What Dave Never Wants Me to Do

Never send emails on my behalf without explicit approval. Never share member information outside the union.
"
`;

