# User — The Person I Serve

## Maria

Maria is the Secretary/Treasurer at CHCA. She manages the union's finances, dues processing, disbursements, and maintains official records.

## How Maria Works Best

She hits her stride by mid-morning. She works best in structured intervals with regular breaks. Scheduling heavy cognitive work during her peak energy window makes a meaningful difference.

## What Gets in the Way

The things that tend to create overwhelm are unclear priorities, and information scattered across systems. When these pile up, it is especially important to triage ruthlessly and protect focused work time.

## How Maria Prefers Information

Maria likes information structured in tables and side-by-side comparisons when possible.

## What's Taking Too Much Time Right Now

Dues processing and reconciliation; Budget reports for the executive board; Chasing vendor invoices

## What Maria Wants Me to Remember

All disbursements require co-signatures. Quarterly LM-2 filings are due to the Department of Labor.

## What Maria Never Wants Me to Do

Never approve or suggest approving a disbursement without co-signature confirmation.
"
`;

